# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback. CF Pages serves static files first;
# any path without a matching prerendered file falls through to the
# rule below. Without this, `/lobby/<id>`, `/join/<code>` and any
# other non-indexable client route fell back to `/index.html` — the
# prerendered homepage — which flashed the homepage chrome on the
# browser before TanStack Router could route to the requested URL.
#
# Target `/_spa-shell.htm` after three failed earlier attempts:
#   1. `/200.html` — CF strips `.html` → `/200` → no file → loop.
#   2. `/_spa-shell/` (directory) — CF strips trailing `/` → loop.
#   3. `/_spa-shell` (no extension) — no loop, but CF served as
#      `application/octet-stream`, browser downloaded the file.
#
# `.htm` is an alternate HTML extension: CF's MIME table maps it to
# `text/html` (so the browser renders), but CF's "Pretty URLs"
# canonicalization specifically targets `.html` (and `/index.html`),
# not `.htm` — so the URL is stable and the rewrite resolves to the
# file directly.
#
# Status `200` is a rewrite (URL stays put), not a redirect.
/*  /_spa-shell.htm  200
